#  We should consider catching {{Throwable}} to make it more robust. 
# {{out.close}} may throw an exception that will hide the original problem, we probably should just  catch and log it without throwing, to make sure that the original exception is thrown

Please add a whitespace after {{catch}}

I apologize if it seems like I'm nitpicking here, but I really don't like catching Throwable.

Our usual idiom for this kind of thing is:

{code}
boolean success = false;
try {
  out = ...
  success = true;
} finally {
  if (!success) {
    IOUtils.cleanup(out)
  }
}
{code}

This avoids the need to wrap the exception (or to rethrow the exception at all).

Thanks again for taking this one up, and sorry for the nitpick!
